Climate change is expected to cause an increase in weather-related hazards, which can severely affect livestock, especially in developing countries. Researchers and policymakers agree that the most significant impact of climate change can be seen in the livestock sector (
 Thornton, 2010; 
 Naqvi and Sejian, 2011). However, most of the work on climate change has focused on the crop sector, and only a few studies have documented the impact of climate change on livestock productivity (
 Thornton etÂ al., 2009; 
 IPCC, 2014).
